column1: 1942,"WN304","Maps","MapContrib is a site similar to uMap that allows a simple [generating](http://mapcontrib.xyz/) of your own map. Example maps include [fire hydrants](http://www.cartes.xyz/t/s8c2d9-Les_bornes__incendie), [mail boxes](http://www.cartes.xyz/t/2c4196-Boites_aux_lettres) andr [bicycle parking](http://www.cartes.xyz/t/s8c2d5-Combien_de_vlos_peut_on_accrocher)."

2206,"WN309","Maps","User Escada [is writing](http://www.openstreetmap.org/user/escada/diary/38884) about his use cases of the online thematic map service MapContrib. A summary of new features of  [MapContrib version 0.8.0 ](https://lists.openstreetmap.org/pipermail/talk/2016-June/076132.html) has also been posted by developer Frederic."

3483,"WN334","Did you know that …","... the service [MapContrib](https://www.mapcontrib.xyz/) of Guillaume AMAT? User escada [presented](http://www.openstreetmap.org/user/escada/diary/38884) it on the basis of a map with dog parks a few months ago."

3604,"WN336","Did you know that …","... the page [mapcontrib](https://mapcontrib.xyz/)? It is up with new features: The ability to create heat maps a new tag and presets handling and has the theme creator to translate all the theme information in English, French and Italian (for now)."

3667,"WN338","Maps","[Mapcontrib](https://mapcontrib.xyz/) has reached version 1.0 and therefore [published](https://blog.mapcontrib.xyz/2017/01/mapcontrib-1-0-is-here/) a first descriptive blog post."

5840,"WN382","Mapping","Through a [Twitter moment](https://twitter.com/i/moments/930853727535329280), user [sev_osm](https://www.openstreetmap.org/user/sev_osm) showcased over 10 outreach and training workshops on CarteInnov run by Les Libres Geographes (LLG) and local OSM mappers. This project supported by International Organization of Francophonie (OIF) aims at building an open map of Digital Innovation stakeholders in Haiti, Madagascar and 12 African countries. The data is hosted in OSM and edited with [MapContrib](https://carteinnov.francophonelibre.org/t/ca1a3e-CarteInnov#)."

10799,"WN490","Community","The [local community of contributors](https://twitter.com/hashtag/osmph) to OpenStreetMap in Manila, Philippines organised its first LGBTQI-themed [MapBeks](https://www.facebook.com/mapbeks) mapathon, training newcomers to add data to OSM using [MapContrib](https://www.mapcontrib.xyz/). Check out Mikko's OSM Diary [post](https://www.openstreetmap.org/user/ockim16/diary/391518)."

10978,"WN494","Did you know that …","... the tag `memorial=ghost_bike`? To remember cyclists killed in traffic, [ghost cycles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghost_bike) are placed at the location of the accident. They can be mapped with [`memorial=ghost_bike`](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Tag:memorial%3Dghost_bike) in conjunction with `historic=memorial`. [This mapcontrib](https://www.mapcontrib.xyz/t/d2b038-Ghost_bikes_witte_fietsen) shows all known ghost bikes; please help to add the missing ones, especially since [the website inspiring the tag](http://ghostbikes.org/) seems to be unmaintained."

15612,"WN605","Did you know that …","... Bruno Duyés' [OpenPianosMap](https://github.com/brunetton/OpenPianosMap)? The goal of this project is to create an open source map of accessible pianos. Doudouosm [said](https://en.osm.town/@Doudouosm/107824898724143697) on Mastodon: '... with its companion [MapContrib](https://www.mapcontrib.xyz/t/e5c83c-OpenPianosMap) theme, it's never been easier to add the ones you run across'."
